parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Media Control Unit (MCU) can cause the loss of various safety-critical functions, including the rearview camera, defrost/defog controls, and exterior turn signal lighting, increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: The main infotainment screen freezes or goes black
the vehicle's instrument cluster is unavailable
the backup camera is not visible
and the HVAC controls are inoperable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the charging system can cause the vehicle to overheat or catch fire, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle's charging system malfunctions
causing the vehicle to pull excessive amps
overheat
or catch fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the high voltage battery system can cause the vehicle to shut down while driving, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle's high voltage battery system fails
causing the vehicle to shut down while driving
resulting in the loss of power and functionality.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front suspension can cause the wheel to jam into the wheel well, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The front suspension has collapsed
the wheel is jammed into the wheel well
the tire has rubbed against the inside of the fender and worn a hole through it
the steering knuckle has snapped in half
the wheel is hanging sideways out of the wheel well.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear suspension can cause the wheel to jam into the wheel well, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The rear suspension has collapsed
the wheel is jammed into the wheel well
the tire has rubbed against the inside of the fender and worn a hole through it.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering knuckle can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The steering knuckle has snapped in half
the wheel is hanging sideways out of the wheel well
the airbags have not deployed
and there is no visible damage to the car that would explain the failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the MCU can cause the screen to lock up, leaving the turn indicators unusable and the defroster deactivated, which can lead to accidents or other safety issues.
symptoms: The MCU is slow to respond to inputs
the screen has locked up
the turn indicators are unusable
the defroster is deactivated.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Drive Unit Water Damage and Corrosion
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water damage and corrosion in the drive unit can cause the vehicle to malfunction or fail to operate, leading to potential safety risks and leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle operates normally one day
but then fails to start or operate properly the next day
with no warning signs or symptoms prior to failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle shifting to neutral while in motion can cause loss of control, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle shifts to neutral while driving
often accompanied by an unknown warning light
and may recur daily when depressing the brake pedal.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Abnormal Humming Sound from Drive Unit
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The abnormal humming sound from the drive unit can indicate a potential failure of the drive unit, which can lead to vehicle malfunction or failure, causing safety risks and inconvenience.
symptoms: An abnormal humming sound is detected coming from the drive unit
often without any warning lights or symptoms.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Computer Problems and Failure to Start
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Computer problems can cause the vehicle to fail to start, leaving the driver stranded, and potentially leading to safety risks and inconvenience.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to start
with no warning signs or symptoms prior to failure
and may be accompanied by computer problems.
